dct_alternative_sm: Veertig jaarige reys togt der kinderen Israels uyt Aegypten
dct_description_sm: Coordinates approximate and based on Greenwich meridian.
Shows topography, drainage, places of historical interest.
Features illustrations throughout of settlements, structures, caravans of travelling Israelites, and a compass rose.
Decorative cartouche with illustrations of Israelites.
"11" ; "Tome. i Page ug" -- right bottom corner.
Appears in Covens, Johannes and Mortier's Cornelis, Atlas antiquus. Amsterdam, 1725, Map no. 11. A reprint of the 1705 Pieter Mortier's edition.
